PRETORIA Callies have cancelled club activities, including their end of the year function with an immediate effect, as a result of a Covid-19 threat. The club has confirmed that two of their players have tested positive for coronavirus. “We have also received instructions that all players and members of the technical committee must quarantine with immediate effect. Based on this we instruct that all club activities and end year function be cancelled,” said Callies CEO Ali Netshifhefhe.   